In this article, President Barack Obama issues a proclamation declaring June 14 as Flag Day and the week beginning on June 14 as National Flag Week. He emphasizes the significance of the American flag as a symbol of the nation's values and history. The proclamation calls on all Americans to display the flag during this week and to honor America by celebrating its heritage and reciting the Pledge of Allegiance. The president directs federal government buildings to display the flag during National Flag Week. The article highlights the role of the flag in uniting Americans and representing the ideals of freedom and liberty.